Purpose: Fix A1 HIGH finding: promote subgroup-stratified accuracy to a full sub-stage with cohort dimensions, per-cohort metrics, sample-size minimums, disparity-alert thresholds, and named ownership

[49m[38;5;9m- 366     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Subgroup-stratified accuracy must be visible.** Voicemail ASR has worse accuracy on certain demographic groups (older speakers, non-native English speakers, speakers with hearing loss who modulate their voice differently). The pipeline must surface accuracy metrics stratified by language preference, age cohort, and (where data permits) accent group. Disparities exceeding configured thresholds should alert. This is not an optional analytics nice-to-have; it is the mechanism by which the institution detects whether the system is silently underserving specific patient populations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Subgroup-stratified accuracy must be visible.** Voicemail ASR has worse accuracy on certain demographic groups (older speakers, non-native English speakers, speakers with hearing loss who modulate their voice differently). The pipeline must surface accuracy metrics stratified by cohort, with explicit architectural support for detecting and alerting on disparities.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Cohort-dimension allow-list: preferred language (from patient record or detected language), age cohort (from matched patient record), geographic region (inferred from area code or patient address), accent group (inferred from acoustic features where the ASR vendor exposes them), and primary insurance type (a coarse SES proxy from the patient record).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Per-cohort metrics: time-to-callback by urgency tier, ASR average word confidence, classifier accuracy (validated by sampled human review), default-to-human-review rate, emergent-classification rate, repeat-caller rate, and queue-depth time (how long voicemails from each cohort sit before staff action).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Per-cohort sample-size minimums for statistical reliability: >=100 voicemails per cohort per measurement window produces reliable metrics; 30-99 voicemails produces noisy metrics with wide confidence intervals (flag as provisional); <30 voicemails is suppressed into an "all_other" bucket rather than reported as a separate cohort (the sample is too small for meaningful inference).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Disparity-alert thresholds: time-to-callback gap >30 minutes for routine items or >5 minutes for urgent items; ASR confidence gap >5 points between any two cohorts; default-to-human-review rate gap >10 points; classifier accuracy gap >5 points. These thresholds are starting points; the equity-monitoring committee calibrates them against the institution's tolerance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Named ownership: the equity-monitoring committee or clinical-quality officer owns the subgroup-stratified dashboard, reviews monthly, and produces a quarterly written summary of disparity trends and remediation actions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The voicemail-specific stake is important to name: the async-queue dynamics amplify underlying accuracy disparities beyond the raw accuracy gap. Lower-confidence cohorts default to human review at a higher rate, and human-review voicemails wait longer in a busy queue because they require more staff time. The result is a structural delay in responsiveness experienced by exactly the populations the pipeline most needs to monitor. The mitigation is both technical (conservative routing posture for low-confidence items, priority-boost for human-review items so they do not age in the queue) and operational (the equity dashboard makes the amplification visible so the institution can respond).
